09/07/2007
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- New High Representative Miroslav Lajcak met with leaders of the religious communities in BiH on Sunday (July 8th), including the Reis-ul-Ulema Mustafa ef.
Ceric of the Islamic Community, Metropolitan Nikolaj of the Serb Orthodox Church, Monsignor Mato Zovkic of the Catholic Church, and Jakob Finci of the Jewish Community.
Lajcak briefed them about his efforts to reach political compromise on key reforms and discussed how religious leaders could help build trust among communities and boost the reconciliation process.
On Monday, Lajcak is in Brussels for talks with EU security chief Javier Solana.
(Dnevni Avaz, Nezavisne Novine - 09/07/07;
RTRS, Fena, OHR website - 08/07/07)
